CAROLINE:
Rory, come down.

36:11.637 --> 36:12.971
What did you see?

36:13.004 --> 36:14.139
What?

36:14.172 --> 36:16.074
The name of the movie,
what was it?

36:16.107 --> 36:18.877
Sex With a Paranoid Guy.
It was a comedy.

36:18.910 --> 36:20.746
Now go home,
you freak.

36:20.779 --> 36:22.414
Where were you?

36:22.448 --> 36:23.815
Fuck you!

36:23.849 --> 36:25.484
(Grunting)

36:25.517 --> 36:26.952
CAROLINE:
Are you okay?

36:26.985 --> 36:28.153
He was older.

36:28.186 --> 36:29.621
He's a 32-year-old guy,

36:29.655 --> 36:31.923
and I'm madly in love
with him, okay?!

36:31.957 --> 36:33.892
Did you have sex
with him?

36:38.497 --> 36:40.399
You did.

36:42.601 --> 36:44.169
(Grunting)

36:44.202 --> 36:46.338
Hey, hey, hey!

36:46.372 --> 36:47.739
Never hit a girl!

36:47.773 --> 36:50.075
Never hit a girl!
Get the hell out of here!

36:50.108 --> 36:52.711
Get out of here!
You want to go to jail?!

36:54.780 --> 36:55.981
(Door closing)

36:56.014 --> 36:57.516
(Breathing heavily)

36:57.549 --> 36:59.485
You want to tell me
what that was about?

37:01.587 --> 37:04.890
Just go, please.

37:04.923 --> 37:07.926
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

37:10.696 --> 37:11.963
Mark...

37:16.535 --> 37:17.703
thanks.

37:23.642 --> 37:27.479
KATIE:
Turns out they were engaged
the whole time.

37:27.513 --> 37:29.881
They moved in together.

37:31.950 --> 37:33.719
I'm such a retard.

37:33.752 --> 37:35.821
Oh, sweetheart,

37:35.854 --> 37:37.923
I wish you would have told me
about it sooner.

37:37.956 --> 37:39.124
I could have warned you.

37:39.157 --> 37:40.459
Never get mixed up
with someone

37:40.492 --> 37:42.961
if there's a third party
involved.

37:42.994 --> 37:44.863
You almost always lose.

37:46.465 --> 37:47.999
You didn't sleep with him,
did you?

37:48.033 --> 37:49.134
Of course not.

37:49.167 --> 37:51.269
I'm sorry. Had to ask.

37:55.774 --> 37:58.444
Aren't you going to wish me
a happy birthday?

37:58.477 --> 38:01.447
Oh, sweetie,
I'm so sorry.

38:03.014 --> 38:04.683
Happy birthday.

38:07.519 --> 38:10.722
So, what do you want to do
to celebrate?

38:11.957 --> 38:13.992
I don't know.

38:14.025 --> 38:17.363
KATIE, NARRATING:
Thank God my name's
not really Katie

38:17.396 --> 38:20.832
and I'm 100% invisible
to the world,

38:20.866 --> 38:24.336
or I'd be so humiliated
by my life right now

38:24.370 --> 38:26.805
I'd probably kill myself.

38:31.710 --> 38:34.346
Do you stay friends
with your exes?

38:34.380 --> 38:37.349
Only if they can handle us
being platonic.

38:37.383 --> 38:39.485
Hasn't happened yet.

38:39.518 --> 38:41.887
Do you pee
in swimming pools?

38:41.920 --> 38:44.490
That's the only place.

38:44.523 --> 38:47.292
What's your favourite thing
in your bedroom?

38:47.325 --> 38:49.160
My heart.

38:49.194 --> 38:52.964
What's your least favourite
thing in your bedroom?

38:52.998 --> 38:54.600
My heart.

38:55.967 --> 38:58.637
What are you listening to
these days?

38:58.670 --> 39:01.773
A voice in my head telling me
that something wonderful

39:01.807 --> 39:03.875
is going to happen
any minute.

39:03.909 --> 39:05.511
It just has to.

39:05.544 --> 39:07.779
MARGARET:
I know the prices
are outrageous,

39:07.813 --> 39:09.581
but you just can't beat
the organic produce.

39:09.615 --> 39:12.117
Absolutely. The meats
are to die for.
Oh, I know.

39:12.150 --> 39:13.619
The other day
I got a leg of lamb.

39:13.652 --> 39:15.320
I'm telling you
it was this big.

39:15.353 --> 39:16.922
Hang on one second.
Is he down?

39:16.955 --> 39:18.123
Yup, boom.

39:18.156 --> 39:19.324
Oh, good.

39:19.357 --> 39:21.593
Did I mention
you look adorable?

39:21.627 --> 39:23.361
Oh, well,
I don't feel it.

39:23.395 --> 39:25.497
Barely got two hours of sleep
last night.

39:25.531 --> 39:28.166
Excitement about
Santa's arrival, or boy trouble?

39:28.199 --> 39:29.668
KATIE:
Boy trouble.

39:29.701 --> 39:31.269
Well, good riddance,
whoever he is.

39:31.302 --> 39:32.404
You can do better.

39:32.438 --> 39:33.839
Couldn't do worse.

39:33.872 --> 39:35.073
I have a nephew.
Oh.

39:36.708 --> 39:39.210
Onwards and upwards.
KATIE: Cheers.

39:39.244 --> 39:41.413
I thought we were the bad guys.

39:41.447 --> 39:43.381
MAN:
Well, no, no, no.

39:43.415 --> 39:44.616
People are people.

39:44.650 --> 39:47.118
You know, red, white, purple.

39:47.152 --> 39:48.954
We're all shit.

39:48.987 --> 39:52.123
You know what else
the Apache enjoyed?

39:52.157 --> 39:53.959
Sodomy.

39:55.326 --> 39:58.029
Most of Custer's
seventh brigade,

39:58.063 --> 40:02.133
second cavalry,
they were found buck naked,

40:02.167 --> 40:04.503
all torn up inside.

40:04.536 --> 40:07.305
Well, Ollie, listen,
it's been a riot.

40:07.338 --> 40:09.908
Cornflower blue.

40:09.941 --> 40:13.011
You're a real blond,
aren't you?

40:13.044 --> 40:14.580
Oh, yeah.

40:14.613 --> 40:16.915
You're real naughty too.

40:16.948 --> 40:18.684
Not tonight. Not-- Not--

40:18.717 --> 40:21.152
Not feeling it tonight,
turtleneck, okay?

40:21.186 --> 40:23.054
Now let me go
before I scream.

40:23.088 --> 40:25.356
(Laughing):
Whoa!

40:25.390 --> 40:26.892
(Imitating Indian war whoop)

40:30.796 --> 40:32.998
PAUL:
You better slow down there.

40:33.031 --> 40:34.466
That stuff will kill you.

40:34.500 --> 40:36.101
I still have
to drive home.

40:36.134 --> 40:37.402
You having fun?

40:37.435 --> 40:39.638
At my own party?
Not a chance.

40:45.310 --> 40:47.078
We've got to stop
meeting like this.

40:47.112 --> 40:48.814
Maggie will get
suspicious.

40:48.847 --> 40:50.482
Really?

40:56.387 --> 41:03.361
*

41:03.394 --> 41:06.498
* Snow is falling

41:06.532 --> 41:10.235
* Do you hear those winter bells
ringing

41:10.268 --> 41:12.971
* In this winter storm?

41:13.004 --> 41:15.406
JOEL, OVER ANSWERING MACHINE:
Hey, uh, Merry Christmas Eve.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.208
It's Joel again.

41:17.242 --> 41:18.710
You never call me back,

41:18.744 --> 41:20.378
so I assume you're either
really busy

41:20.411 --> 41:22.447
or you hate Jews.

41:22.480 --> 41:24.149
(Laughing)

41:24.182 --> 41:26.552
So here's why
I keep calling.

41:26.585 --> 41:28.053
The third week of school

41:28.086 --> 41:30.088
I tried to jump
out of a dorm window.

41:30.121 --> 41:33.424
And I remember you spent some
time at a mental hospital,

41:33.458 --> 41:35.260
and I thought you might
be able to relate

41:35.293 --> 41:37.362
to what I'm going through,
and then we could be friends.

41:37.395 --> 41:38.964
My bad.

41:40.298 --> 41:43.535
* Take it in, take it in

41:43.569 --> 41:47.873
* And sing your Christmas song

41:51.476 --> 41:54.079
* The world is changing

41:54.112 --> 41:58.049
* Everything is painted
white and red

41:58.083 --> 42:00.185
* And gold

42:01.653 --> 42:03.889
* The stars are dangling...

42:09.494 --> 42:11.563
Oh.

42:16.467 --> 42:18.336
(Sniffing)

42:18.369 --> 42:20.405
Thank you so much.

42:20.438 --> 42:21.940
You're welcome.

42:23.975 --> 42:25.276
Oh, Dad.

42:26.878 --> 42:29.180
What did I do
to deserve this?

42:29.214 --> 42:30.982
You knocked up Mom.

42:35.220 --> 42:37.455
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

42:37.488 --> 42:40.926
Oh, these will keep
my nuts warm.

42:43.094 --> 42:44.696
Thank you, kid.

42:57.776 --> 42:59.577
How was dinner
with your family?

43:00.679 --> 43:02.313
Oh, thank you for asking.

43:02.347 --> 43:03.749
My--

43:03.782 --> 43:05.951
Don't ever spend Christmas Eve
with old Hindus.

43:07.886 --> 43:10.155
It was like Gunga Din meets
the Brothers Grimm.

43:10.188 --> 43:12.257
I couldn't get out of there
fast enough.

43:12.290 --> 43:14.192
(Doug chuckling)

43:14.225 --> 43:16.194
Oh, here.

43:17.528 --> 43:19.931
I know what
my baby girl likes.

43:30.075 --> 43:32.110
Thanks.

43:32.143 --> 43:34.279
It's beautiful.

43:41.687 --> 43:43.989
DOUG:
I used to be your hero.

43:48.593 --> 43:50.628
Bet you don't even
remember that, do you?

43:50.662 --> 43:52.798
Not really.

43:52.831 --> 43:57.335
I used to come home from work,
you'd just go crazy.

43:59.070 --> 44:03.108
You'd grab my hand, show me your
latest Barbie or whatever.

44:06.011 --> 44:08.413
Then the witch
kicked me out.

44:08.446 --> 44:11.616
Right before Christmas, too.

44:11.649 --> 44:15.987
You latched on
like a goddamn pit bull.

44:17.588 --> 44:19.390
Wouldn't let go.

44:19.424 --> 44:20.859
Seriously?

44:22.427 --> 44:24.429
Screaming your lungs out.

44:29.367 --> 44:32.337
I can't believe
I don't remember that.

44:37.342 --> 44:38.576
(Turning TV on)

44:38.609 --> 44:40.311
CROWD, OVER TV:
Happy New Year!

44:40.345 --> 44:42.513
KATIE, NARRATING:
Right after Rory and I
broke up,

44:42.547 --> 44:44.682
Jade found
a new boyfriend.

44:44.716 --> 44:46.718
I had no one to celebrate with
last night.

44:46.752 --> 44:47.886
(Knocking on door)

44:47.919 --> 44:49.921
CAROLINE:
Honey? It's me.

44:49.955 --> 44:51.189
Come in.

45:00.231 --> 45:02.167
Oh, God.

45:02.200 --> 45:03.434
Dad's dead?

45:08.774 --> 45:10.208
Oh, my God!

45:10.241 --> 45:12.177
Congratulations!

45:13.779 --> 45:18.016
I don't even know
what to say.

45:18.049 --> 45:20.385
She's marrying the moustache.

45:20.418 --> 45:22.387
RORY, OVER PHONE:
Oh, no!

45:22.420 --> 45:24.756
I knew you'd understand.

45:24.790 --> 45:27.458
Come over, please.

45:29.060 --> 45:31.229
Uh...

45:31.262 --> 45:32.697
first I, uh,

45:32.730 --> 45:34.632
I got to tell you something.

45:34.665 --> 45:36.234
(Whispering):
Shit.

45:37.435 --> 45:38.970
(In normal voice):
Hold on.

45:48.613 --> 45:50.648
Okay, what?

45:50.681 --> 45:53.451
Okay, um...

45:53.484 --> 45:58.123
so the night we broke up
I took two sleeping pills.

45:58.156 --> 46:02.994
And Jade was over trolling on
4chan with my roommates.

46:04.729 --> 46:06.965
So, any resolutions?

46:06.998 --> 46:10.335
Well, I found out my boyfriend's
boning my best friend.

46:10.368 --> 46:12.871
I thought you and your boyfriend
broke up.

46:12.904 --> 46:15.807
We did.
Now it's permanent.

46:15.841 --> 46:18.243
I'm never going to speak
to either of them again.

46:18.276 --> 46:19.644
Smart choice.

46:19.677 --> 46:20.979
What about you?

46:21.012 --> 46:24.315
I am going back to work
part-time.

46:24.349 --> 46:26.451
Wow, really? So soon?

46:26.484 --> 46:27.919
Yeah, well,
I feel great.

46:27.953 --> 46:30.488
You know, I got my body back.
Why not?

46:30.521 --> 46:32.858
Paul's pissed.

46:32.891 --> 46:34.659
If he had his way
I'd stay home forever

46:34.692 --> 46:36.394
and be a broodmare.

46:36.427 --> 46:38.864
Do you know
what that is?

46:38.897 --> 46:40.798
Like a sad horse.

46:40.832 --> 46:42.100
Close, yeah.

46:42.133 --> 46:44.269
One that does nothing
but give birth.

46:45.904 --> 46:48.073
Do you want to have
more kids?

46:48.106 --> 46:49.207
No.

46:54.712 --> 46:56.447
(Cell phone vibrating)

47:01.352 --> 47:04.022
(Laughing)

47:04.055 --> 47:06.057
(Indistinct chattering)

47:17.869 --> 47:19.304
How's it going?

47:19.337 --> 47:21.706
Wow, you're even prettier
than I remember.

47:21.739 --> 47:23.308
And you're just
as sweet.

47:23.341 --> 47:24.675
Um...

47:24.709 --> 47:27.845
I can't believe you finally
decided to hang out with me.

47:27.879 --> 47:30.615
I hope I don't destroy
your social standing.

47:30.648 --> 47:32.617
Stop it.

47:33.952 --> 47:35.887
What made you finally
call me back?

47:35.921 --> 47:38.223
Your text made me laugh.

47:39.925 --> 47:41.659
Hey, you're legal, right?

47:41.692 --> 47:43.294
Yeah.
You should order wine.

47:43.328 --> 47:45.396
They won't card me here
if you do it.

47:54.072 --> 47:57.208
So anyway,
long story short,

47:57.242 --> 47:59.744
they've been fucking
ever since.

47:59.777 --> 48:01.947
What a roll you're on.

48:01.980 --> 48:06.084
I know. I have the worst luck
with guys.

48:06.117 --> 48:08.286
Yeah, I would say
the worst taste.

48:08.319 --> 48:11.156
I mean, you're the one
who picks them, right?

48:11.189 --> 48:12.457
Yeah.

48:12.490 --> 48:15.026
Anyway, it seems like your
problems go way beyond guys.

48:15.060 --> 48:16.861
I mean, you're confused
about a lot.

48:16.894 --> 48:18.896
Well, who isn't at our age?

48:18.930 --> 48:21.032
And that's why
the most important thing

48:21.066 --> 48:23.368
is to develop
self-awareness.

48:23.401 --> 48:25.536
I'm pretty much the most
fucked-up person I know,

48:25.570 --> 48:29.474
and I'm working really hard
to understand myself.

48:31.176 --> 48:32.877
Are you?

48:32.910 --> 48:36.314
Working really hard
to understand you?

48:36.347 --> 48:37.815
Not really.

48:37.848 --> 48:40.185
(Both laughing)
(Footsteps approaching)

48:40.218 --> 48:42.087
WAITER:
When you're ready.

48:52.797 --> 48:54.399
Right.

48:56.534 --> 48:58.436
(Vibrating)

49:07.678 --> 49:10.448
Hello?
(Woman sobbing over phone)

49:11.682 --> 49:14.319
Who is this? Affie?

49:15.653 --> 49:18.056
What is it?
Is it my dad?

49:18.089 --> 49:20.058
Affie, what's wrong?!

49:20.091 --> 49:22.060
DOCTOR:
You can see him now.

49:24.095 --> 49:25.730
KATIE, NARRATING:
When he fell,

49:25.763 --> 49:28.566
an artery in the sac
around his brain ripped open.

49:28.599 --> 49:30.968
They fixed it
and stopped the bleeding,

49:31.002 --> 49:34.239
but now all they can do
is wait and see.

49:44.449 --> 49:46.484
(Machinery hissing
and beeping)

49:59.830 --> 50:01.366
(Sniffling)

50:18.616 --> 50:20.451
(Typing)

50:43.174 --> 50:46.177
I used to pour my dad
his beers for him.

50:46.211 --> 50:50.648
Even though I get how sad
and inappropriate that is,

50:50.681 --> 50:53.284
at the time it made me feel
really special.

50:55.553 --> 50:57.122
And I'm still an expert
at pouring beer

50:57.155 --> 51:00.091
so that the foam
doesn't spill over.

51:03.894 --> 51:06.431
Oh, uh, one more--

51:06.464 --> 51:07.998
One more thing.

51:08.032 --> 51:10.868
My dad and I, we used to play
this game together

51:10.901 --> 51:12.703
when we were watching TV,

51:12.737 --> 51:17.041
and I would ask him if I could
have some of his beer.

51:17.074 --> 51:19.277
So he would reach over
to grab his mug,

51:19.310 --> 51:22.680
and when he did
I would flop my mouth down

51:22.713 --> 51:24.815
on his beer belly and...

51:24.849 --> 51:27.685
(Lips sputtering)

51:31.222 --> 51:34.759
And he would get all mad,
like I had tricked him.

51:34.792 --> 51:36.527
And...

51:36.561 --> 51:39.597
I would just
laugh my head off.

52:00.851 --> 52:02.887
(Knocking)

52:08.959 --> 52:10.428
Yes.

52:12.830 --> 52:14.332
Hi, my name's Amy Graham.

52:14.365 --> 52:16.967
I'm a student
of Professor Gallo's.

52:17.001 --> 52:19.036
I hate bothering him at home,

52:19.069 --> 52:21.071
but it's really,
really important,

52:21.105 --> 52:22.607
and I lost
his phone number.

52:22.640 --> 52:24.842
Oh, I'm sorry.
He's not home.

52:26.977 --> 52:29.914
Darn it. Okay, okay.

52:29.947 --> 52:31.349
Uh...

52:31.382 --> 52:34.319
But I'll be happy
to give him a message.

52:34.352 --> 52:36.621
Will you please tell him there's
been a death in my family,

52:36.654 --> 52:38.956
so I can't finish
my paper on time.

52:38.989 --> 52:41.726
Which paper?

52:42.860 --> 52:44.795
The one he assigned.

52:46.431 --> 52:49.367
All right. I'm sorry.

52:49.400 --> 52:51.869
I mean, for your loss.

52:51.902 --> 52:53.504
That's okay.

52:53.538 --> 52:54.739
Merci.

52:54.772 --> 52:56.341
Bye.

53:04.715 --> 53:06.116
(Sighing)

53:06.150 --> 53:07.752
(Heart beating)

53:16.026 --> 53:18.296
KATIE, NARRATING:
During the week of work
I missed,

53:18.329 --> 53:19.997
Margaret kept her resolution

53:20.030 --> 53:23.033
and got a job redoing
a zillionaire's media room.

53:23.067 --> 53:24.635
For the next month

53:24.669 --> 53:27.372
she'll be working weekdays
from 9:00 to 3:00.

53:30.941 --> 53:33.611
So Kyle doesn't get
too traumatized by the change,

53:33.644 --> 53:36.447
Paul's going to eat lunch
at home every day.

53:43.654 --> 53:46.557
Well, I can't believe
how okay you seem.

53:46.591 --> 53:49.560
He had cirrhosis
for a long time.

53:49.594 --> 53:51.195
I knew he was going to die.

53:51.228 --> 53:52.830
I was pretty much
prepared for it.

53:52.863 --> 53:53.998
(Chuckling)

53:54.031 --> 53:55.500
The arrogance
of youth.

53:56.867 --> 53:58.068
Don't say that.

53:58.102 --> 54:01.038
No, no, I mean it
as a compliment.

54:01.071 --> 54:04.275
An ironic one, but if young
people weren't so arrogant,

54:04.309 --> 54:06.110
they'd really
be in trouble.

54:06.143 --> 54:08.145
What do you mean?

54:08.178 --> 54:09.747
Look, life kicks your ass.

54:09.780 --> 54:11.582
If young people knew it,
they'd crawl into the basement

54:11.616 --> 54:13.284
with a crack pipe
and never come out.

54:13.318 --> 54:17.788
Wouldn't take risks
or fight for lost causes,

54:17.822 --> 54:19.957
or even start a career.
I mean, why bother, right?

54:22.527 --> 54:24.729
You think you're okay
with your dad's death?

54:24.762 --> 54:27.432
Not a chance. It won't even
hit you that he's really gone

54:27.465 --> 54:28.999
until you're in your 30's,

54:29.033 --> 54:32.136
which happens to be the most
difficult decade of life.

54:32.169 --> 54:36.273
That is when the shit
really hits the fan.

54:37.942 --> 54:39.477
(Sighing)

54:41.111 --> 54:42.980
What are you grinning at?

54:43.013 --> 54:45.383
You.

54:45.416 --> 54:47.452
Tell me more.

54:48.653 --> 54:50.855
I want to know
everything.

54:52.757 --> 54:54.559
MARGARET:
Hey, you haven't quit yet.

54:54.592 --> 54:56.361
KATIE: Not yet.
MARGARET: See you later. Thanks.

54:56.394 --> 54:58.062
KATIE: Yeah!
PAUL: Hey, hey. Hi, sweetie.

54:58.095 --> 55:00.631
I'll be right back.

55:00.665 --> 55:03.067
Here's your salary,
and a little something extra.

55:04.769 --> 55:06.203
Thanks. Bye.

55:06.236 --> 55:07.738
PAUL:
Bye.

55:18.716 --> 55:20.250
PAUL:
"Dear Miss Kampenfelt,

55:20.284 --> 55:21.852
"since you expressed
a desire today

55:21.886 --> 55:23.754
"to learn more
about adult life,

55:23.788 --> 55:25.723
"here are 10 bitter truths
for your reading pleasure.

