01:17:37.754 --> 01:17:39.522
You understand, right?

01:17:39.555 --> 01:17:41.190
I'm sorry.

01:17:41.224 --> 01:17:42.759
It's going to be okay.

01:17:43.993 --> 01:17:45.194
Okay.

01:17:47.630 --> 01:17:49.298
Oh, God.

01:17:49.332 --> 01:17:52.601
KATIE, NARRATING:
Being pregnant is like
being seasick,

01:17:52.635 --> 01:17:54.771
and you can't
get off the boat.

01:17:56.172 --> 01:17:58.775
The smell of bubble gum,
deodorant,

01:17:58.808 --> 01:18:04.948
scented candles makes me want
to vomit from my toes.

01:18:04.981 --> 01:18:06.349
(Groaning)

01:18:09.986 --> 01:18:11.721
(Panting)

01:18:15.925 --> 01:18:18.527
(Phone line ringing)

01:18:18.561 --> 01:18:20.229
DAN, OVER PHONE:
Hello?

01:18:20.263 --> 01:18:22.265
I'm pregnant.

01:18:22.298 --> 01:18:23.900
And the baby's yours.

01:18:23.933 --> 01:18:25.769
So I thought maybe
before I got an abortion,

01:18:25.802 --> 01:18:27.603
you'd like to discuss it.

01:18:27.636 --> 01:18:29.205
Dwayne, you know better.

01:18:29.238 --> 01:18:31.274
You got to call me
during my office hours, okay?

01:18:31.307 --> 01:18:32.876
Good night.
Wait...

01:18:33.777 --> 01:18:35.211
(Cell phone beeping off)

01:18:35.244 --> 01:18:37.280
(Screaming)

01:18:37.313 --> 01:18:38.882
(Sobbing)

01:18:40.083 --> 01:18:42.618
SHERMAN:
You don't need antidepressants,

01:18:42.651 --> 01:18:45.554
because you're not
clinically depressed.

01:18:45.588 --> 01:18:47.490
You're grieving.

01:18:47.523 --> 01:18:49.926
There's a world
of difference.

01:18:49.959 --> 01:18:52.762
Not just for your father.

01:19:01.304 --> 01:19:03.840
KATIE, NARRATING:
When I was in the second grade
I liked to gross boys out

01:19:03.873 --> 01:19:05.942
by eating flies and ants.

01:19:05.975 --> 01:19:08.444
Even a daddy longlegs once.

01:19:10.146 --> 01:19:12.982
